let _markdown = "\n\n## 3D Chromatin Conformation Capture\n\nChromatin conformation capture technologies reveal how DNA is organized in three-dimensional space within the nucleus.\n\n## Hi-C\n\n**Hi-C** captures genome-wide chromatin interactions without protein specificity.\n\n* Unbiased, genome-wide contact map\n* Reveals TADs, compartments, and loops\n* Requires 1-10M cells\n\n## ChIA-PET\n\n**ChIA-PET** combines ChIP with proximity ligation for protein-specific interactions.\n\n* Protein-specific interactions (CTCF, RNAPII, cohesin)\n* High signal-to-noise ratio\n* Requires 10-50M cells\n\n## HiChIP\n\n**HiChIP** combines Hi-C with ChIP for low-input protein-specific mapping.\n\n* Protein-specific interactions\n* Low input (100K-1M cells)\n* Cost-effective alternative to ChIA-PET\n\n## Key Differences\n\n| Feature             | Hi-C                | ChIA-PET          | HiChIP          |\n| ------------------- | ------------------- | ----------------- | --------------- |\n| Input cells         | 1-10M               | 10-50M            | 100K-1M         |\n| Protein specificity | No                  | Yes               | Yes             |\n| Best for            | Genome architecture | Specific proteins | Low-input loops |\n\nSee [comparison page](../comparison) for detailed protocol comparison.\n";
